Name = "☳☶plug - SEARCH STALK"
Description = "Monitor incoming distributed searches and log matching activity to JSONL with local HTML UI viewing.\n\nWatch Modes:\n  W:<term>\n    Wildcard substring match (case-insensitive)\n\n  E:<term>\n    Exact full-query match (case-insensitive)\n\n  U:<user>\n    Exact username match (case-sensitive)\n\nCommands:\n  /ss_wild <term>\n    Add wildcard watch rule\n\n  /ss_exact <term>\n    Add exact watch rule\n\n  /ss_user <user>\n    Add username watch rule\n\n  /ss_remove <term|user>\n    Remove a watch rule\n\n    Explicit removal examples:\n      /ss_remove W:<term>\n      /ss_remove E:<term>\n      /ss_remove U:<user>\n\n  /ss_list\n    Show current watch rules\n\n  /ss_ui\n    Generate/open SearchStalk HTML log viewer\n\n  /ss_wishlist\n    Generate/open wishlist UI\n    (queries repeated 3+ times per user)\n\nLogging:\n  - Matched searches are always written to hits.json\n  - log_wildcard/log_exact/log_user only affect event viewer output\n  - Optional log rotation and retention cleanup supported\n\nAuto-Add Options:\n  - Add users from public room chat\n  - Add users from private messages\n  - Add queued upload users\n  - Add users on wildcard hits\n  - Add users on exact hits\n  - Add resolved users\n  - Add privileged users\n  - Add users joining/leaving rooms\n\nNotes:\n  - Uses append-only JSONL logging\n  - Includes local HTML UI rendering\n  - Designed for Nicotine+ 3.3.10"
